Urban area in mid-north Sweden, administrative centre of Jämtland County and commune. The city was the only Swedish city founded and chartered in the 18th century. Östersund is the region's cultural and economical centre and by tradition a city of trade and commerce. There are many winter sports facilities. As the most centrally located city in Sweden, the city credits itself as the centre of Sweden
